# Minime Alpine world (RK3566) — board-specific package set.
#
# RK3566 ships Mali Bifrost G52 (Rockchip).  The Mali driver pair
# (libmali / mali_kbase) is intentionally absent in V1: the kernel has
# CONFIG_MALI_KBASE=n and Mesa Panfrost is the GLES provider.  This is
# the V1 acceptance target (Anbernic RG ARC-D).  Vulkan stays out of V1
# per the implementation plan; PanVK would require a separate driver
# discussion and is intentionally not in this list.
#
# Board-specific deltas:
#   - RK3566 supports DMC devfreq + PSCI CPU idle, both enabled by the
#     common + rk3566 kernel config fragments.  No extra userspace
#     packages are needed beyond world-common.
#   - The thermal watchdog is in-kernel (CONFIG_THERMAL with
#     DEVFREQ_THERMAL + the Rockchip DFI driver); RK3566's existing
#     S15thermal-watchdog init script is replaced by the OpenRC thermal
#     service in minime-overlay.

# Inherit world-common behavior is provided by build.sh, which concatenates
# world-common and world-<board> at install time.  This file currently
# contributes no extra packages, but is preserved so the board delta
# remains explicit and version-controllable.
